🔁 Day 59: Learn Deque in Java (ArrayDeque vs LinkedList) – Implement Stack and Queue with Deque
🔹 Why this?
Deque (Double-Ended Queue) is a powerful data structure used in many problems like sliding window maximum, palindromes, and LRU cache. Java provides ArrayDeque which is faster than Stack/LinkedList in many cases.

☑️ What to cover in Day 59:
Introduction to Deque

What is Deque?
Operations: addFirst(), addLast(), pollFirst(), pollLast(), etc.

ArrayDeque vs LinkedList as Deque
Performance differences

When to use which?
Implement Stack using Deque

LIFO behavior using addFirst() and removeFirst()
Implement Queue using Deque

FIFO behavior using addLast() and removeFirst()
Real-world use case or problem (Optional):

Try solving "Sliding Window Maximum" (Leetcode #239)



Operation	    Description (English)	                                Hinglish Explanation
addFirst(E e)	Adds element e to the front (head) of the deque.	    Front seat pe bitha diya banda. Starting point pe element ko insert karta hai.
addLast(E e)	Adds element e to the end (tail) of the deque.	        Last seat pe bitha diya. Queue ke end mein element add karta hai.
pollFirst() 	Removes and returns the first element of the deque.
                Returns null if empty.	Pehle aaya, pehle gaya.         Front wale element ko hata deta hai.
pollLast()	    Removes and returns the last element of the deque.      Queue ke end se element hata deta hai — jaise last passenger utar gaya.
                Returns null if empty.
peekFirst()	    Returns the first element without removing it.	        Front seat pe kaun hai dekh lete hai — bina hataaye.
peekLast()	    Returns the last element without removing it.	        Last seat pe kaun baitha hai, bas dekhne ke liye.


push(E e)	Inserts element e at the front of the deque                 Jaise ek plate ka stack — naya plate upar chadha diya.
            (like stack’s push).
pop()	Removes and returns the first element (like stack’s pop).       Upar wala plate utha liya — jo sabse last mein aaya tha, wahi pehle gaya.
        Returns exception if empty.


⚠️ Note: pop() agar queue empty ho toh exception throw karta hai, jabki pollFirst() sirf null return karta hai — yaani zyada safe hai poll.
